Language name: DANGALEAT
Language number: 4374
Alternate names: Dangla
Classification: Afro-Asiatic, Chadic
Comments: Dangaleat is spoken in a mountainous area of 
central Chad near Mongo. There are 2 level tones. Vowels 
appear both long and short in the first syllable of words. 
All consonants can be geminated.

Sources: 

Fedry, J. 1977. Apercu sur la phonologie et la tonologie 
de quatre langues du groupe "Mubi-Karbo" (Guera) 
(Dangaleat-est, Dangaleat-ouest, Bidiyo, Dyongor). Etudes 
Phonologiques Chadiennes, Caprile.